(37, 6, 'Testing ng mga Gangster sa Malolos', NULL, 'What possible background, concerns, and/or interest of the audience that may have shaped how the message was received? Sample ItoDuterte’s remarks hark back to an incident from 1989 when he was a mayor. Despite the controversial nature of his comments, many of his supporters dismissed them as a joke (BBC News, 2016).What was/were the objectives of the speech?What was/were the reasons for addressing the specific issue?This speech took place in 2016 during the presidential election. Considering the context of the event and the period it occurred, one can clearly ascertain that Duterte\'s objective in his speech was to promote his track record, his platforms, his character, and his political app', 0, '2023-12-08 02:31:12', '2023-12-11 11:06:55', '2023-12-07 19:31:12', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\" id=\"isPasted\"><strong><em><u>What possible background, concerns, and/or interest of the audience that may have shaped how the message was received?&nbsp;</u></em></strong></p><p>Sample Ito</p><p><em>Duterte&rsquo;s remarks hark back to an incident from 1989 when he was a mayor. Despite the controversial nature of his comments, many of his supporters dismissed them as a joke (BBC News, 2016).</em></p><p>What was/were the objectives of the speech?</p><p>What was/were the reasons for addressing the specific issue?</p><p><br></p><p>This speech took place in 2016 during the presidential election. Considering the context of the event and the period it occurred, one can clearly ascertain that Duterte&#39;s objective in his speech was to promote his track record, his platforms, his character, and his political approach.</p><p>However, when it comes to the brief mention of the controversial rape joke about 36-year-old Jacqueline Hamill, who was gang-raped and killed by inmates during a jail siege in Davao City (Murdoch, 2016), the specific intent was to showcase his unfiltered speech, his decisive commands, and perhaps an edgy sense of humor.</p><p>From both the dialogue in his anecdote and his choice of words, punctuated with frequent profanity, one can deduce that Duterte intended to convey that he spoke without filters and would voice whatever was on his mind. This was further cemented by Duterte&rsquo;s statement, &ldquo;I do not want anybody controlling my mouth. I say what I say, and I&#39;ve said it. If it does not sit well with you, that&#39;s your problem,&quot; (Duterte as cited in Murdoch, 2016).</p><p>Duterte emphasized his assertive leadership style by ordering his men to simply &ldquo;bury the criminals in one hole&rdquo; (ABS-CBN News, 2016), especially since the perpetrators (already deceased) had committed heinous acts in their lifetimes, including rape and murder. This approach was a major focal point of Duterte&#39;s 2016 campaign. Statements such as, &ldquo;Those who destroy the lives of our children will be destroyed&rdquo; and &ldquo;Those who kill my country will be killed. Simple as that. No middle ground. No apologies. No excuses&rdquo; (France, 2016) were prevalent throughout his campaign, solidifying his reputation as a leader with an &ldquo;Iron Fist.&rdquo;</p><p>Additionally, he sought to promote his unique and edgy sense of humor, aiming to connect with everyday Filipinos and distancing himself from the elite and traditional politicians. Clearly, this rape joke was a flawed attempt at such humor given the backlash it received. The controversy escalated to the point where he felt compelled to apologize for his comments: &ldquo;I apologize to the Filipino people for my recent remarks in a rally. There was no intention of disrespecting our women and those who have been victims of this horrible crime. Sometimes my mouth can get the better of me,&rdquo; (Duterte as cited in Ranada, 2016).</p><p>Regardless of the nature of his remarks, the speech and the anecdote he narrated at the Amoranto Sports Complex in Quezon City underscored his aim to present himself as candid in his speech, assertive in his directives, and possessing a distinctive and relatable sense of humor.</p>', 'public'),
(38, 7, 'This house would NOT ban immediate relatives of corrupt politicians from Running for office', NULL, '<p style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;text-align:center;\" id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:21px;\">Leader of Opposition&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:21px;\">(Negative)</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Clarify Status Quo/Problem&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:&quot;Cal', 0, '2023-12-08 05:45:14', NULL, '2023-12-07 22:45:14', '<p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;text-align:center;\' id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:21px;\">Leader of Opposition&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:21px;\">(Negative)</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Clarify Status Quo/Problem&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">This house would NOT ban immediate relatives of corrupt politicians from Running for office. Well, it really<strong>&nbsp;</strong>depends on the person&rsquo;s involvement to the corruption of their immediate relative. But for the sake of this debate, let us assume that they are only immediate relatives of the corrupt politicians&mdash;there&rsquo;s no official verdict whatsoever about their involvement in such crime.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Counter Policy&nbsp;</span></strong><em><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">(if applicable)</span></em><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">:&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;margin-bottom:9.85pt;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">1.&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Intensive background check</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;margin-bottom:9.85pt;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">2.&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">3.&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><em><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Banner:&nbsp;</span></em></strong></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><em><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Directly Oppose:&nbsp;</span></em></p><div style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><ul style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;\"><li style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">No because it would produce a culture where prejudices based on familial background are acceptable and actually promoted.</span></li></ul></div><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><em><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Even if analysis:&nbsp;</span></em></p><div style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><ul style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;\"><li style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Even if they were immersed in the deeds of&nbsp;the said corrupt politician simply by being in their presence, what&#39;s preventing us from saying that they would incorporate those memories and deeds they witnessed as a reference to prevent further corruption?</span></li></ul></div><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><em><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Assume that its true:&nbsp;</span></em></p><div style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><ul style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;\"><li style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Assuming<em>&nbsp;</em>that<em>&nbsp;</em>banning them reduces the risk of promoting more corrupt politicians in the office. It is also true that it could deprive the people of possible great leaders to lead them towards betterment.</span></li></ul></div><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Argument #1 Banner:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Banning people from running for office because of their familial relationship with corrupt politicians is unreasonable and amounts to prejudice against them.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Premise:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Last I checked, judging people based on factors they cannot control was incorrect. When we have preconceived opinions not supported by facts, logic, and/or actual experiences, I believe the correct term is prejudice.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Logical Reason</span></strong>: <strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">That&#39;s pretty much what the state will do if they deny aspiring candidates the opportunity to run for office because of people&#39;s genetic resemblance and legal relationship to a criminal.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Evidence/Example:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Even if we move beyond incumbency, it would be extremely frustrating if an institution prevented us from achieving our goals because of what someone close to us did rather than our own expertise and our own accomplishments.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Conclusion:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">It is indeed unfair, unjustified, and childish to hold people accountable to the point of depriving them of their aspirations because of the actions of a close relative&mdash;when, in fact, all of them are adults capable of making their own decisions.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Argument #2 Banner:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Upon banning people based on trivial reasons,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>the state<strong>&nbsp;</strong>would produce a culture where prejudices based on familial background are acceptable and actually promoted.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Premise:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">The<strong>&nbsp;</strong>state<strong>&nbsp;</strong>and the laws it legislates is one of the main driving factors and influence on shaping the culture of the society under it.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Logical Reason:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">That is why if they legislate such an outrageous law, it will create an idea that it is only appropriate to judge people, not on who they are as an individuals but rather their family tree&mdash;specifically that one person who does some really bad stuffs. That way of thinking will be accepted and promoted.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;text-align:justify;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Evidence/Example:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">In the eyes of the normal citizens, if it wasn&rsquo;</span>t appropriate to begin with, why would the government allow it?</p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><strong>Conclusion:&nbsp;</strong>The government, along with its people, is what inevitably define the culture of a society. If the government promotes prejudice among its people, the backlash that would happen after math would be troublesome to say the least.</p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Argument #3 Banner:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;Assuming that banning immediate relatives of corrupt politicians reduces the risk of promoting more corrupt politicians to office. It is also true that it could deprive the people of possible great leaders to lead them towards betterment.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Premise:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">We are dealing with probability here, so it is not certain that there will only be one outcome.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Logical Reason:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">It is critical to reduce the risk of corrupt politicians. The issue here is the reason given to justify the banning process. If they were not proven beyond a reasonable doubt to be guilty of political corruption like their close relative, who are we to say that the risk of them being corrupt themselves is so high that the only solution is to prevent them from running for office?&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Evidence/Example:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Furthermore, by prohibiting prospective politicians, the state deprives itself and the people of a potentially exemplary leader&mdash;as opposed to their criminal immediate relative counterpart.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Conclusion</span>:&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">The reduction of risk and the deprivation of possibly great leaders are two of the much more possible repercussion of banning immediate relatives of corrupt politicians. Now the big question: is the reason heavy and solid enough to deprive people of potential revolutionary leaders equally? I don&rsquo;t think so.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Argument #4 Banner:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Even if they were immersed in the deeds of&nbsp;the said corrupt politician simply by being in their presence, what&#39;s preventing us from saying that they cannot incorporate those memories and deeds they witnessed as a reference to prevent further corruption?</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Premise:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Being aware of a specific piece of knowledge does not imply that one will automatically agree, follow that knowledge, or apply it in a literal sense.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Logical Reason:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">If the leader is aware of such wickedness and crookedness throughout the system, he or she will not be exploited due to naivet&eacute;. Nobody requires a non-threatening leader to represent and guide them. Competence should be the primary characteristic that anyone looks for in a leader. And one of the primary indicators of competence is being aware of and knowledgeable about people&#39;s proclivity to do evil.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Evidence/Example:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Suppose a leader understands the processes and how things work in various political corruptions. In that case, he or she can use that knowledge to benefit the state and its people because the leader will find it easier to get inside the heads of the perpetrators of political corruption.</span></p><p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;\'><strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Conclusion:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;Knowledge is everything in this world. One who has knowledge with potentially harmful moral implications does not necessarily have to be morally corrupt themself. It will all depend on how the said bearer can and will use it.</span></p>', 'public'),
(39, 4, 'Transcendental Encounter', NULL, '<p style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;text-align:center;\" id=\"isPasted\">Dr. Jordan Peterson, a famous Canadian psychology professor, changed my perception of life to an unimaginable degree. I was an ignorant little boy when I stumbled into one of Dr. Jordan Peterson\'s videos on <em id=\"isPasted\">Youtube</em>. In the said video, he talked about a somewhat controversial topic of legislation of the usage of the personal pronoun in Canada. His rat', 0, '2023-12-08 05:48:56', NULL, '2023-12-07 22:48:56', '<p style=\'margin:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;color:black;text-align:center;\' id=\"isPasted\">Dr. Jordan Peterson, a famous Canadian psychology professor, changed my perception of life to an unimaginable degree. I was an ignorant little boy when I stumbled into one of Dr. Jordan Peterson&#39;s videos on <em id=\"isPasted\">Youtube</em>. In the said video, he talked about a somewhat controversial topic of legislation of the usage of the personal pronoun in Canada. His rationale and line of thinking are by no means top-notch, but what captivates me the most is how he could deliver his thoughts in a well-constructed and articulated manner. That video was just the first of many viewings I did of him. As it turns out, Dr. Peterson also posted his classes online for free&mdash;not a bad price, I suppose. His contents are a composition of psychology, politics, religion, and philosophy. As I binge-watched his videos, I learned and realized many things. I learned to read more, write more (becoming articulate in the process), and think holistically (not focusing on one side and digging deeper). Upon doing all of this, I got to develop my writing skills, belief system, values, philosophy, and my ultimate goal in life. These videos of him lecturing shift my conscious mind from an ignorant, go-with-the-flow way of thinking to a think for yourself, grow up, and take responsibility for your own life way of thinking. Now that I have this foundation, striving for my dream of leaving a particular legacy behind in this world is not far out of reach after all.</p>', 'public'),
